<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,611,2030]" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,727,753]" pageId="8" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis</emphasis>
Glandular sclerites well developed; strong seta on ventral surface of P-II; genital plates somewhat isosceles trapezoid-shaped; postgenial sclerite outstretched and rectangle shaped; genital plates fused anteriorly, separated posteriorly and fused with postgenial sclerite in male; acetabula reduced in size.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
